wikipedia_page.main: Kerry Payne (née Shacklock, born 30 October 1971) is an English former synchronised swimmer. She represented Great Britain at the 1992 Olympic Games in Barcelona, finishing seventh in the solo event and sixth in the duet with Laila Vakil. She also won two bronze medals at the 1993 European Championships, and is a four-time Commonwealth Games silver medalist.
